<dl id="un1005ab"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1005">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1005ab"> (NLI.3) 5(ab)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Edgeworth (Maria): Castle Rackrent</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In 1800 <mark>MARIA EDGEWORTH</mark> opened, with <mark><cite>Castle Rackrent</cite></mark>, the long series of her popular, moral, and fashionable tales. Their local colouring and distinctively Irish character made them noticeable; but even the warm praise of Scott and the more durable value of her stories for children have not prevented Miss Edgeworth from becoming obsolete. <small> Edmund Gosse, <a name="EGSH" href="/udra/udex.htm#EGSH"><cite title="source">A Short History of Modern English Literature</cite></a> (1897), 295</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Maria Edgeworth (1767-1849), English novelist. </mm> </dd></dl>
